description: Li₂CuSb crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. There are two inequivalent Li¹⁺ sites. In the first Li¹⁺ site, Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. All Li(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.167 Å. In the second Li¹⁺ site, Li(2)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiSb₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cu(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Li(2)Sb₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Cu(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra. All Li(2)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.743 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form CuSb₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Li(2)Sb₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Cu(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Li(2)Sb₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.743 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 14-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Li(2)¹⁺, six equivalent Li(1)¹⁺, and four equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.

NaBiF₆ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form NaF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Bi(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 41°. All Na(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.340 Å. Bi(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form BiF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Na(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 41°. All Bi(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.048 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a bent 150 degrees geometry to one Na(1)¹⁺ and one Bi(1)⁵⁺ atom.

K₂PtSe₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (3.387 Å) and four longer (3.455 Å) K(1)-Se(1) bond lengths. Pt(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pt(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.512 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to six equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Pt(1)²⁺ atoms.

Rb₂O₂ is alpha boron-derived structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. Rb(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1) atoms. There are four shorter (2.855 Å) and two longer (2.936 Å) Rb(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1) is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Rb(1) and one O(1) atom. The O(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.527 Å.

ZrPtSn is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Zr(1) is bonded to four equivalent Pt(1) and six equivalent Sn(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted corner and face-sharing ZrSn₆Pt₄ tetrahedra. All Zr(1)-Pt(1) bond lengths are 2.781 Å. All Zr(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 3.211 Å. Pt(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Zr(1) and four equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Pt(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 2.781 Å. Sn(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Zr(1) and four equivalent Pt(1) atoms.

TaCu₃Te₄ is Sulvanite structured and crystallizes in the cubic P̅43m space group. Ta(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form TaTe₄ tetrahedra that share edges with six equivalent Cu(1)Te₄ tetrahedra. All Ta(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.668 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form CuTe₄ tetrahedra that share corners with eight equivalent Cu(1)Te₄ tetrahedra and edges with two equivalent Ta(1)Te₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.619 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Ta(1)⁵⁺ and three equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing TeTaCu₃ tetrahedra.

AgI is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AgI₄ tetrahedra. All Ag(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.876 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing IAg₄ tetrahedra.

RbF is Tetraauricupride structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.992 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ atoms.

BaPdS₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Ba(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 3.186-3.450 Å. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pd(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.387 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing SBa₄Pd₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-68°.

HfNiSn is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Hf(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ni(1) and six equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Hf(1)-Ni(1) bond lengths are 2.648 Å. All Hf(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 3.057 Å. Ni(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Hf(1) and four equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Ni(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 2.648 Å. Sn(1) is bonded in a distorted q6 geometry to six equivalent Hf(1) and four equivalent Ni(1) atoms.

Cs₂TiS₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to three equivalent S(2)²⁻ and four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Cs(1)-S(2) bond distances ranging from 3.686-3.861 Å. There are a spread of Cs(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 3.524-3.555 Å. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one S(2)²⁻ and four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing TiS₅ trigonal bipyramids. The Ti(1)-S(2) bond length is 2.241 Å. All Ti(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.417 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to six equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one Ti(1)⁴⁺ atom.

RbH₃O₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two RbH₃O₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 1, 0) direction. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.954 Å) and two longer (3.003 Å) Rb(1)-O(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent H¹⁺ sites. In the first H¹⁺ site, H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one O(2)²⁻ atom. The H(1)-O(2) bond length is 0.981 Å. In the second H¹⁺ site, H(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to one O(1)²⁻ and one O(2)²⁻ atom. The H(2)-O(1) bond length is 1.031 Å. The H(2)-O(2) bond length is 1.589 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent H(2)¹⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one H(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent H(2)¹⁺ atoms.

CuAlCl₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal P̅42c space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CuCl₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Al(1)Cl₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.353 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form AlCl₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cu(1)Cl₄ tetrahedra. All Al(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.168 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Cu(1)¹⁺ and one Al(1)³⁺ atom.

SrFBr is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (3.264 Å) and one longer (3.470 Å) Sr(1)-Br(1) bond length. All Sr(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.540 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Br(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.398 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and face-sharing FSr₄Br₄ tetrahedra.

Sr₃Ti₂O₇ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. There are two inequivalent Sr²⁺ sites. In the first Sr²⁺ site, Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and five equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. All Sr(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.671 Å. There is one shorter (2.501 Å) and four longer (2.794 Å) Sr(1)-O(2) bond lengths. In the second Sr²⁺ site, Sr(2)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(3)²⁻ and eight equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form SrO₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with four equivalent Sr(2)O₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with four equivalent Sr(2)O₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with eight equivalent Ti(1)O₆ octahedra. All Sr(2)-O(3) bond lengths are 2.787 Å. All Sr(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.791 Å. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻, one O(3)²⁻, and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form TiO₆ octahedra that share corners with five equivalent Ti(1)O₆ octahedra and faces with four equivalent Sr(2)O₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-2°. The Ti(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.970 Å. The Ti(1)-O(3) bond length is 2.005 Å. All Ti(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.971 Å. There are three inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, two equivalent Sr(2)²⁺, and two equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and one Ti(1)⁴⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OSr₅Ti octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 8°. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent Sr(2)²⁺ and two equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

RuP₂ is zeta iron carbide structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnnm space group. Ru(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent P(1)¹⁻ atoms to form RuP₆ octahedra that share corners with eight equivalent Ru(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent P(1)PRu₃ tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent Ru(1)P₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 56°. There are two shorter (2.361 Å) and four longer (2.387 Å) Ru(1)-P(1) bond lengths. P(1)¹⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ru(1)²⁺ and one P(1)¹⁻ atom to form PPRu₃ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Ru(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with thirteen equivalent P(1)PRu₃ tetrahedra, and  an edgeedge with one P(1)PRu₃ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 68-71°. The P(1)-P(1) bond length is 2.247 Å.

CuBS₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form CuS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent B(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.278 Å. B(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form BS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent B(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All B(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 1.952 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent B(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SCu₂B₂ tetrahedra.

Cs₂O₂ is alpha boron-derived structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. Cs(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1) atoms. There are four shorter (2.979 Å) and two longer (3.200 Å) Cs(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1) is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Cs(1) and one O(1) atom. The O(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.518 Å.

CoAsS is Ilmenite-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pca2₁ space group. Co(1)²⁺ is bonded to three equivalent As(1) and three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form CoAs₃S₃ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Co(1)As₃S₃ octahedra, corners with three equivalent As(1)Co₃S tetrahedra, and corners with three equivalent S(1)Co₃As tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 63-65°. There are a spread of Co(1)-As(1) bond distances ranging from 2.363-2.369 Å. There are a spread of Co(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 2.278-2.288 Å. As(1) is bonded to three equivalent Co(1)²⁺ and one S(1)²⁻ atom to form distorted AsCo₃S tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Co(1)As₃S₃ octahedra, corners with six equivalent As(1)Co₃S tetrahedra, and corners with nine equivalent S(1)Co₃As tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 77-80°. The As(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.323 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Co(1)²⁺ and one As(1) atom to form distorted SCo₃As tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Co(1)As₃S₃ octahedra, corners with six equivalent S(1)Co₃As tetrahedra, and corners with nine equivalent As(1)Co₃S tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 77-81°.

LiAsF₆ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form LiF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent As(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 31°. All Li(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.079 Å. As(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form AsF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Li(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 31°. All As(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 1.772 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a bent 150 degrees geometry to one Li(1)¹⁺ and one As(1)⁵⁺ atom.

OsAs₂ is zeta iron carbide structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnnm space group. Os(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent As(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OsAs₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 54°. There are two shorter (2.470 Å) and four longer (2.508 Å) Os(1)-As(1) bond lengths. As(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Os(1)²⁻ atoms.

SrWN₃ crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. There are two inequivalent Sr²⁺ sites. In the first Sr²⁺ site, Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to one N(1)+2.67-, one N(4)+2.67-, two equivalent N(2)+2.67-, two equivalent N(3)+2.67-, and two equivalent N(5)+2.67- atoms. The Sr(1)-N(1) bond length is 2.658 Å. The Sr(1)-N(4) bond length is 2.719 Å. There is one shorter (2.635 Å) and one longer (2.848 Å) Sr(1)-N(2) bond length. There is one shorter (2.740 Å) and one longer (2.860 Å) Sr(1)-N(3) bond length. There is one shorter (2.630 Å) and one longer (2.818 Å) Sr(1)-N(5) bond length. In the second Sr²⁺ site, Sr(2)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to one N(1)+2.67-, one N(4)+2.67-, two equivalent N(3)+2.67-, two equivalent N(5)+2.67-, and two equivalent N(6)+2.67- atoms. The Sr(2)-N(1) bond length is 2.653 Å. The Sr(2)-N(4) bond length is 3.077 Å. There is one shorter (2.680 Å) and one longer (2.781 Å) Sr(2)-N(3) bond length. There is one shorter (2.597 Å) and one longer (3.336 Å) Sr(2)-N(5) bond length. There is one shorter (2.648 Å) and one longer (2.667 Å) Sr(2)-N(6) bond length. There are two inequivalent W⁶⁺ sites. In the first W⁶⁺ site, W(1)⁶⁺ is bonded to one N(2)+2.67-, one N(5)+2.67-, one N(6)+2.67-, and two equivalent N(1)+2.67- atoms to form distorted corner-sharing WN₅ trigonal bipyramids. The W(1)-N(2) bond length is 2.133 Å. The W(1)-N(5) bond length is 1.799 Å. The W(1)-N(6) bond length is 2.062 Å. There is one shorter (1.881 Å) and one longer (2.044 Å) W(1)-N(1) bond length. In the second W⁶⁺ site, W(2)⁶⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to one N(2)+2.67-, one N(3)+2.67-, one N(6)+2.67-, and two equivalent N(4)+2.67- atoms. The W(2)-N(2) bond length is 2.075 Å. The W(2)-N(3) bond length is 1.805 Å. The W(2)-N(6) bond length is 1.875 Å. There is one shorter (2.027 Å) and one longer (2.051 Å) W(2)-N(4) bond length. There are six inequivalent N+2.67- sites. In the first N+2.67- site, N(1)+2.67- is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one Sr(1)²⁺, one Sr(2)²⁺, and two equivalent W(1)⁶⁺ atoms. In the second N+2.67- site, N(2)+2.67- is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, one W(1)⁶⁺, one W(2)⁶⁺, and one N(4)+2.67- atom. The N(2)-N(4) bond length is 1.446 Å. In the third N+2.67- site, N(3)+2.67- is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, two equivalent Sr(2)²⁺, and one W(2)⁶⁺ atom. In the fourth N+2.67- site, N(4)+2.67- is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to one Sr(1)²⁺, one Sr(2)²⁺, two equivalent W(2)⁶⁺, and one N(2)+2.67- atom. In the fifth N+2.67- site, N(5)+2.67- is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, two equivalent Sr(2)²⁺, and one W(1)⁶⁺ atom. In the sixth N+2.67- site, N(6)+2.67- is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to two equivalent Sr(2)²⁺, one W(1)⁶⁺, and one W(2)⁶⁺ atom.

AgI is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4m2 space group. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AgI₄ tetrahedra. All Ag(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.878 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing IAg₄ tetrahedra.

SiC is Moissanite-6H structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. There are three inequivalent Si⁴⁺ sites. In the first Si⁴⁺ site, Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(2)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(1)-C(2) bond length is 1.898 Å. All Si(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 1.894 Å. In the second Si⁴⁺ site, Si(2)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(3)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(2)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(2)-C(3) bond length is 1.898 Å. All Si(2)-C(2) bond lengths are 1.895 Å. In the third Si⁴⁺ site, Si(3)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(1)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(3)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(3)-C(1) bond length is 1.904 Å. All Si(3)-C(3) bond lengths are 1.896 Å. There are three inequivalent C⁴⁻ sites. In the first C⁴⁻ site, C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(3)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra. In the second C⁴⁻ site, C(2)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(1)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(2)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra. In the third C⁴⁻ site, C(3)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(2)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(3)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra.

KBr is Tetraauricupride structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. All K(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.502 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Rb₂PtC₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Pt(1)²⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-Pt(1) bond lengths are 3.474 Å. Pt(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to six equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent C(1) atoms. Both Pt(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 1.987 Å. C(1) is bonded in a linear geometry to one Pt(1)²⁻ and one C(1) atom. The C(1)-C(1) bond length is 1.276 Å.

LiCuO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing LiO₆ octahedra. There are two shorter (2.143 Å) and four longer (2.156 Å) Li(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Cu(1)³⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.853 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Cu(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OLi₃Cu₂ square pyramids.

PON₁ is Anatase-derived structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic Cc space group. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to two equivalent N(1)³⁻ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing PN₂O₂ tetrahedra. There is one shorter (1.567 Å) and one longer (1.569 Å) P(1)-N(1) bond length. There is one shorter (1.617 Å) and one longer (1.618 Å) P(1)-O(1) bond length. N(1)³⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent P(1)⁵⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent P(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

CdGeP₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form CdP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cd(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Ge(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Cd(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.586 Å. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form GeP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ge(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Cd(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Ge(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.364 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Ge(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing PCd₂Ge₂ tetrahedra.

BaS is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BaS₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Ba(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 3.229 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SBa₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

OsAl₂ is Titanium Disilicide-like structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Os(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to ten equivalent Al(1) atoms. There are eight shorter (2.624 Å) and two longer (2.819 Å) Os(1)-Al(1) bond lengths. Al(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Os(1) and five equivalent Al(1) atoms. There are four shorter (2.689 Å) and one longer (2.697 Å) Al(1)-Al(1) bond length.

O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one H(1)¹⁺ atom. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms.

Al₂O₃ is Corundum structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3c space group. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge, corner, and face-sharing AlO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 48-60°. There are three shorter (1.873 Å) and three longer (1.989 Å) Al(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OAl₄ trigonal pyramids.

PbF₂ is Fluorite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Pb(1)²⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Pb(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.597 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FPb₄ tetrahedra.

LiBiS₂ is Caswellsilverite-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Imma space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form LiS₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent Bi(1)S₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with four equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with eight equivalent Bi(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-1°. There are two shorter (2.787 Å) and one longer (2.811 Å) Li(1)-S(1) bond length. There are two shorter (2.792 Å) and one longer (2.807 Å) Li(1)-S(2) bond length. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form BiS₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent Bi(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with four equivalent Bi(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with eight equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-1°. There are two shorter (2.792 Å) and one longer (2.822 Å) Bi(1)-S(1) bond length. There are two shorter (2.787 Å) and one longer (2.836 Å) Bi(1)-S(2) bond length. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SLi₃Bi₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-1°. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SLi₃Bi₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-1°.

ZnCl₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing ZnCl₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.303 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to two equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

K₄CdAs₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. In the first K¹⁺ site, K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing KAs₄ tetrahedra. There is one shorter (3.348 Å) and three longer (3.521 Å) K(1)-As(1) bond lengths. In the second K¹⁺ site, K(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. All K(2)-As(1) bond lengths are 3.488 Å. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. Both Cd(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.520 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to three equivalent K(2)¹⁺, four equivalent K(1)¹⁺, and one Cd(1)²⁺ atom.

BeTe is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Be(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing BeTe₄ tetrahedra. All Be(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.454 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Be(1)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing TeBe₄ tetrahedra.

KZnF₃ is (Cubic) Perovskite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form KF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent K(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent K(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with eight equivalent Zn(1)F₆ octahedra. All K(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.921 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form ZnF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Zn(1)F₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent K(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Zn(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.066 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

NaLaO₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4₁/amd space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.441 Å. La(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing LaO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 18°. There are four shorter (2.441 Å) and two longer (2.475 Å) La(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ONa₂La₃ square pyramids.
